{"id": "1003378", "question": "为什么说皮尔逊相关系数是刻画了线性相关性？", "description": "<div class=\"col-md-11 col-xs-10\"><p>为什么说皮尔逊相关系数是刻画了线性相关性？如果两个变量相关，但是不一定是线性关系，那么用皮尔逊相关系数会怎么样？</p></div>", "viewer": 6409, "tags": ["统计/机器学习", "概率分布", "回归分析", "描述性统计"], "answers": [{"lvl1_answer": "<div class=\"col-md-11 col-xs-10 p-r\"><p>如果有两个变量$X$和$Y$，并且它们的尺度都是-1到1的，那么$X$和$Y$的皮尔逊相关系数就是$X$和$Y$做一元<b>线性回归的回归系数</b>（<a href=\"http://sofasofa.io/forum_main_post.php?postid=1000497\" target=\"_blank\">解释</a>），从这点我们可以看明显的看出，皮尔逊相关系数就是描述的线性关系。</p><p>另外一个反例是，如果$Y=X^2$，并且$X$的范围是-1到1，尽管它们是有关联的，但是它们的皮尔逊系数为0，因为它们并没有任何线性关系。<br/></p></div>", "lvl2_answer": []}, {"lvl1_answer": "<div class=\"col-md-11 col-xs-10 p-r\"><p>\"If a relationship between two variables is not linear, the rate of increase or decrease can change as one variable changes, causing a \"curved pattern\" in the data. This curved trend might be better modeled by a nonlinear function, such as a quadratic or cubic function, or be transformed to make it linear. Plot 4 shows a strong relationship between two variables. However, because the relationship is not linear, the Pearson correlation coefficient is only +0.244.\"</p><p><img data-filename=\"Unknown.png\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"width: 259.5px; height: 191.80434782608694px;\"/><br/></p><p>source: <a href=\"https://support.minitab.com/en-us/minitab/18/help-and-how-to/statistics/basic-statistics/supporting-topics/basics/linear-nonlinear-and-monotonic-relationships/\" target=\"_blank\">https://support.minitab.com/en-us/minitab/18/help-and-how-to/statistics/basic-statistics/supporting-topics/basics/linear-nonlinear-and-monotonic-relationships/</a></p></div>", "lvl2_answer": []}]}